<item>
            <title>[OAK-3377] Two spaces in SQL2 fulltext search -&gt; error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3377</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Execute the following SQL2 query (eg, in crx/de&apos;s query tool)&lt;br/&gt;
SELECT * FROM &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;nt:unstructured&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; AS c WHERE (CONTAINS(c.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;jcr:title&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, &apos;a  b&apos;) AND ISDESCENDANTNODE(c, &apos;/content&apos;))&lt;br/&gt;
(note there are 2 spaces between &quot;a&quot; and &quot;b&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
Result: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Invalid expression: &apos;a b&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there is only 1 space between a and b, there is no error. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Per jsr-283, fulltext expressions should be able to have strings of whitespace.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
